6 An Act relating to the state Medicaid program;
requiring the Oklahoma Health Care Authority to
7 include certain information in annual budget request;
specifying calculation method of certain costs;
8 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-1925.2A of Title 63, unless
14 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority in its annual budget
16 request submitted pursuant to Section 34.36 of Title 62 of the
17 Oklahoma Statutes shall include a supplemental item reflecting the
18 new state and federal funding necessary to meet the additional costs
19 associated with reimbursing nursing facilities and intermediate care
20 facilities for individuals with intellectual disabilities at the
21 most recent audited cost.
22 B. Audited cost shall be calculated by using the latest cost
23 report submitted to the Oklahoma Health Care Authority.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
